Module count

Package count.ds

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IndexedTree
    Public interface used by the algorithms: a rooted ordered tree in which every node is assigned a unique index defined by a depth-first traversal.
    ProfileTable
    Public interface used by the algorithms: a table of family profiles.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnnotatedTable
    Stores a table of family sizes across a number of organisms.
    Heap<T extends Comparable<? super T>>
    A class implementing (min-)priority queue and directory (search for element).
    IntegerOrMissing
    Class for nonnegative integers + missing entries (any negative integer)
    IntegerOrMissing.Renderer
    An appropriate class for displaying these numbers in a Swing JTable: the rounded value appears in the cell but the tool tip text gives the true value.
    Phylogeny  
    Phylogeny.Node
    Implementation for a node in a phylogeny.
    TreeComparator
    Class implementing Day's linear-time algorithm for comparing evolutionary tree topologies.
    TreeTraversal
    Traversal algorithms for an indexed tree.
    TreeTraversal.WellIndexed
    Adapter for any indexed tree to respect the leaves-first order.
    UniqueProfileTable  
    UPGMA
    Direct implementation of the UPGMA algorithm (unweighted pair-group method with arithmetic mean), from dissimilarity/distance.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    UPGMA.ClusteringPolicy
    Different methods for calculating the distances after joining two clusters.
    UPGMA.Dissimilarity
    Statistics to measure the dissimilarity between genomes based on copy numbers.
